Malaysia Stocks: ECS ICT, Hua Yang, Hwang-DBS, Jaya, SapuraCrest

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-03-29T09:17:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/malaysia-stocks-ecs-ict-hua-yang-hwang-dbs-jaya-sapuracrest.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Malaysia  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. close in Kuala
Lumpur.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 5.84, or 0.4
percent, to 1,520.09, the highest since March 9.         ECS ICT Bhd. (ECS)  , a distributor of computer-related
products, rose 3.9 percent to 1.60 ringgit, a record high. The
company said it was awarded distribution rights for Apple Inc.â€™s
iPad in the Southeast Asian nation, according to a stock
exchange filing.        Hua Yang Bhd. (HYB)  , a property developer, jumped 10
percent to 1.52 ringgit, an all-time high. The stock is valued
at 2.76 ringgit each, Terence Wong, an analyst at CIMB
Investment Bank Bhd., wrote in a report today.       Hwang-DBS (Malaysia) Bhd. (HDBS MK), a stock brokerage,
gained 4.4 percent to 2.35 ringgit, the most since Nov. 22. The
company said net income in the second quarter ended Jan. 31 rose
38 percent to 23.2 million ringgit ($7.7 million), according to
a stock exchange filing.        Jaya Tiasa Holdings Bhd. (JT)  , a timber producer and oil
palm planter, advanced 6.5 percent to 6.56 ringgit, its highest
close since March 2000. Jaya said net income in the third
quarter ended Jan. 31 almost tripled from a year earlier to 39.9
million ringgit on higher selling prices, according to a company
statement.  SapuraCrest Petroleum Bhd. (SCRES)  , an oil and gas
services provider, climbed 2.5 percent to 3.64 ringgit, its
steepest gain since March 9. The company said profit in the
fourth quarter ended Jan. 31 surged 79 percent from a year
earlier to 72.7 million ringgit, according to a statement to the
stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
